RIYADH: Saudi Arabia announced one death from COVID-19 and 602 new infections on Tuesday. Of the new cases, 179 were recorded in Riyadh, 149 in Makkah, 122 in Jeddah, 19 in Madinah, 14 in Hofuf, 13 in Dammam, eight in Taif, eight in Al-Mubarraz, seven in Al-Khobar, six in Qatif, five in Tabuk, five in Al-Lith, and four in Jubail. The total number of recoveries in the Kingdom increased to 541,157 after 147 more patients recovered from the virus. A total of 8,873 people have succumbed to the virus in the Kingdom so far. Over 50 million doses of a coronavirus vaccine have been administered in the Kingdom to date.